Zimbabwe â€™s government is seeking $32
million to fund diamond exploration in its Eastern Highlands
region, the  Daily News  reported, citing Deputy Mines Minister
Gift Chimanikire.  The government plans to search for gems after reports of
finds in the mountainous region, the Harare-based newspaper
said. The search will include renewed exploration at the Marange
fields, the Daily News said. So far this year, Marange has
exported diamonds worth about $174 million, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
